@startuml
!theme cerulean

start

:1. User logs into ADIM Configuration Console\n(or uses API/JSON import);
:2. System displays the list of existing Table Mappings

:3. Select or create new Integration Profile;
:4. load a template or existing data.
:5. Choose source table / entity;

if (Table already exists?) then (yes)
    :4. Load existing mapping;
else (no)
    :4. Initialize new mapping template;
endif

:5. Define target file name pattern\n(e.g. ITEM_MASTER_{timestamp}.csv);

repeat
    :6. Add/Edit Field Mapping\n(source_field → target_field, data_type, required, default, XREF...);
    :7. Validate field configuration;
    if (Validation passed?) then (yes)
        :8. Save field rule;
    else (no)
        :9. Show validation error;
        :10. Return to edit field;
    endif
repeat while (More fields to map?) is (yes)

:11. Save complete Table Mapping;

:12. (Optional) Trigger Refresh Meta-Schema Cache;

note right
  Changes take effect after cache refresh
end note

stop

@enduml